277:const partialDelta = parseClaudeCliPartialAssistantDelta({
```

```console
$ node --input-type=module << 'PROOF' ...
=== Production relay function (compiled dist) ===
function parseClaudeCliPartialAssistantDelta(params) {
if (!usesClaudeStreamJsonDialect(params)) return null;
if (params.parsed.type !== "assistant" || !isRecord$1(params.parsed.message)) return null;
const message = params.parsed.message;
if (isRecord$1(message) && message.stop_reason != null) return null;
const partialText = collectCliText(params.parsed.message);
if (!partialText || partialText.length <= params.textSoFar.length) return null;
const delta = partialText.startsWith(params.textSoFar) ? partialText.slice(params.textSoFar.length) : partialText;
if (!delta) return null;
return {
text: partialText,
delta,
sessionId: params.sessionId,
usage: params.usage

=== stop_reason guard behavior ===
Guard present: true
Streaming partial (stop_reason null): forwarded as delta
Complete message (stop_reason non-null): skipped, avoids duplicate
```

- **Observed result after fix:** The production function at `dist/claude-live-session-CVhJM-wp.js:220` contains the `message.stop_reason != null` guard. The function correctly returns null for complete messages (stop_reason non-null), preventing duplicate final messages. Streaming partials (stop_reason absent/null) proceed to compute the text delta and are forwarded as `chat.delta` events. The call site at line 277 invokes this function in the live session handler.
- **What was not tested:** Live Claude CLI session with real streaming output over the gateway WebSocket connection.
